<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-200-094 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 576 139</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  March 18 1991 v220 n11 p30(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mississippi 2000 links schools. (interactive fiber optic-baseddistance learning network)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wilson, Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Mississippi 2000, an interactive fiber optic-based distancelearning network, is connecting Mississippi high school classroomswith teaching facilities by using the public switched network.andO;The network was introduced by a telecommunications industrycoalition led by South Central Bell and Northern Telecom.andP;  Highschools in Clarksdale, Corinth, Philadelphia, and West Point areusing the network, which increases flexibility and reduces costs.andO;The network consists of an MCS 3800 broadband switch, fiberlightwave terminals, digital video codecs, IBM computers linked bylocal area networks, and Apple Macintosh workstations.andP;  Thelessons learned from Mississippi 2000 will be applied to businesseducation and training.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   South Central Bell Telephone Co. (Communication systems)Northern Telecom Inc. (Communication systems).andO;Topic:     EducationFiber OpticsCommunications ApplicationsTelecommunications ServicesMississippiMississippi 2000 (Telecommunication system).andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographmap.andO;Caption:   Mississippi 2000 distance learning network. (map)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>